PN,39502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1772143504
OL,3,CAssisted dying delays are 'reflections
OL,4,Cof good government' UK tells Isle of
OL,5,CMan
OL,7,FJake Richards MP has written in
OL,8,Fresponse to a letter sent by the mover
OL,9,Fof the Manx bill Dr Alex Allinson MHK,
OL,10,Fwhere he asked for for a meeting with
OL,11,Fthe Justice Secretary David Lammy,
OL,12,Fover 'apparent delays'.
OL,14,FMr Richards has responsibility for the
OL,15,FUK's constitutional relationship with
OL,16,Fthe Crown Dependencies, within his
OL,17,Frole as Parliamentary Under-Secretary
OL,18,Foff State for Justice.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,396,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1772143504
OL,3,CAssisted dying delays are 'reflections
OL,4,Cof good government' UK tells Isle of
OL,5,CMan
OL,7,FWithin the letter, Mr Richards wrote:
OL,8,F"The time required to scrutinise Crown
OL,9,FDependency legislation varies
OL,10,Fdepending on its complexity,
OL,11,Fsensitivity, and any legal or
OL,12,Fconstitutional questions that arise.
OL,14,F"This is a collaborative process
OL,15,Fbetween the UK and the Crown
OL,16,FDependencies to ensure that each Bill
OL,17,Freceives appropriate analysis.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,396,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1772143504
OL,3,CAssisted dying delays are 'reflections
OL,4,Cof good government' UK tells Isle of
OL,5,CMan
OL,7,F"The duration of scrutiny is therefore
OL,8,Fnot a reflection of delay by any party
OL,9,Fin the process, but of the need to
OL,10,Fensure that the UK properly fulfils
OL,11,Fits constitutional responsibilities
OL,12,Ffor good government and international
OL,13,Fobligations."
OL,15,FRecent analysis suggests the process
OL,16,Fhas taken 'almost four times longer'
OL,17,Fthan other bills sent from the Isle of
OL,18,FMan to Westminster.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,396,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1772143504
OL,3,CAssisted dying delays are 'reflections
OL,4,Cof good government' UK tells Isle of
OL,5,CMan
OL,7,FA freedom of information (FOI) showed
OL,8,Fthat since the start of 2020, the
OL,9,FMinistry of Justice took an average 88
OL,10,Fdays to process Isle of Man
OL,11,Flegislation.
OL,13,FIt has been more than 300 days since
OL,14,Fthe Bill was put to the UK Government.
OL,16,FMr Richards concluded by writing: "I
OL,17,Frecognise the importance of this
OL,18,Flegislation for Members of Tynwald and
OL,19,Fthe wider community.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,396,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1772143504
OL,3,CAssisted dying delays are 'reflections
OL,4,Cof good government' UK tells Isle of
OL,5,CMan
OL,7,F"UK scrutiny of Crown Dependency
OL,8,Flegislation follows a set process and
OL,9,Ftherefore a meeting to discuss the law
OL,10,Fwould not be appropriate. I trust this
OL,11,Fupdate is helpful in setting out the
OL,12,Fposition and next steps."
OL,14,FPoliticians in several parliaments are
OL,15,Fconsidering assisted dying
OL,16,Flegislation, including in Westminster,
OL,17,Fwhere MPs backed the Terminally Ill
OL,18,FAdults (End of Life) Bill 314 votes to
OL,19,F291, majority 23, in June 2025.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
